quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  79,27,"What, are you more difficult to create or the heaven? God has constructed it"
  79,28,"And on high has He raised its canopy, and He has given it order and perfection"
  79,29,"Its night does He endow with darkness, and its splendor does He bring out"
  79,30,"And the earth, moreover, has He extended"
  79,31,He draws out from there its moisture and its pasture
  79,32,And the mountains has He firmly fixed
  79,33,For use and convenience for you and your livestock
  79,34,"Therefore, when there comes the great overwhelming event"
  79,35,The day when humanity will remember all that they strove for
  79,36,"And hellfire will be placed in full view, for all to see"
  79,37,Then for those who transgressed all bounds
  79,38,And had preferred the life of the present
  79,39,The abode will be hellfire
  79,40,"And for those who had entertained the fear of standing before their Lord, and have restrained their soul from lower desires"
  79,41,Their abode will be the garden
  79,42,"They ask you about the Hour, “When will its appointed time be?”"
  79,43,Are you concerned with the declaration of it
  79,44,With your Lord is the finale
  79,45,You are only a warner for those who fear it
  79,46,"The day they see it, it will be as if they had stayed but a single evening, or until the following morn"